Bielice  is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Biskupiec, within Nowe Miasto County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland. It lies approximately  south-east of Biskupiec,  north-west of Nowe Miasto Lubawskie, and  south-west of the regional capital Olsztyn.
